<TITLE> Families of 3 army officers meet PM </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 3 (bdnews24.com)  Families of three army officers slain at the BDR mutiny saw the prime minister at her residence Tuesday night. The prime minister, Sheikh Hasina, told them that her administration and she personally would always be by their side, her press secretary Abul Kalam Azad said. Heart-rending moments followed when the wives, children and other relatives of Col Nakib, Col Arefin and Major Saleh met with Hasina. The families were in floods of tears and the prime minister and her younger sister Sheikh Rehana also burst into tears. She told them to be patient, Azad said. bdnews
